               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-347-person2438">
                  HENRY 
                  PALMER
               <interp inst="t18290611-347-person2438" type="surname" value="PALMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-347-person2438" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-347-person2438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290611-347-viclabel1821" type="occupation">warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-347-victim2437 t18290611-347-viclabel1821"></join>. On the 28th of April I was passing Bank-buildings, Cornhill - I heard some person call behind me, I turned, and saw the prisoner in custody; I immediately missed my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>JOHN HOLLAND. I am street-keeper of St. Andrews, Holborn. On the 28th of April I saw the prisoner and two others - I followed them, and just at the beginning of <placeName id="t18290611-347-crimeloc1822">Cornhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-347-crimeloc1822" type="placeName" value="Cornhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-347-crimeloc1822" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-347-off1819 t18290611-347-crimeloc1822"></join> I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief from the witness' pocket; he gave it to one of his companions, who escaped; Perry has since identified one of the others, who is brought here on another charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a gentleman, who gave me a load to carry to the Bank; there was a waggon going by, and this gentleman said I had picked his pocket, but I had not.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182906110154"></xptr>SAMUEL HEINSON. I produce a record of the prisoner's former conviction; I was present at his trial - he is the same person (read).</p>
